Argentine Stocks: Aluar Aluminio, Petrobras Argentina

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-22T19:32:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/argentine-stocks-aluar-aluminio-petrobras-argentina.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:15 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.1 percent to 3,325.79.  Aluar Aluminio Argentino SAIC (ALUA AF), the operator of
 South America ’s biggest aluminum smelter, declined 0.6 percent
to 4.85 pesos as a report in  Brazil  showed unemployment
dropping, raising concern that the country’s central bank will
raise rates in July. Aluar, which exports about 72 percent of
its production, counts Brazil as its largest foreign market.
Additionally, the U.S. Federal Reserve lowered forecasts for
growth and employment this year and for 2012.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)  , the local unit of
Brazil’s state-controlled oil company Petroleo Brasileiro SA,
gained 0.6 percent to 8.17 pesos as crude oil for July delivery
rose $1.66, or 1.7 percent, to $95.06 a barrel on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
